The title says "It ain't the second album" but... actually it is :) I bought it together with the first album but it's a completly different story. It's modern, it's catchy and it's got such other style of beats and flava, that u'll know at once, that it ain't American, French or German production. I don't want to say that's wack, no, it's good, original album. The group has not only MCs, but some live instrumentalists too. The interesting thing is Lil Tena, 10-year-old girl, who's making a choruses in one song. The album is worth hearing.
